Rumen Radev Bulgarian police and prosecutors searched the offices of President Rumen Radev Thursday, Radev’s press service said in an email. The raids in the offices of the head of state and one of his advisers are related to two ongoing investigations, BNR public radio reported, citing Chief Prosecutor Ivan Geshev. Radev, elected in 2016 on the ticket of the opposition Socialists, has repeatedly criticized Geshev for targeted probes against high-profile officials. Radev’s legal affairs secretary had been under investigation for influence peddling. He has denied wrongdoing.